Public Domain (US Government work)

The NRLMSISE-00 empirical thermospheric model and its reference
Fortran implementation are released by the US Naval Research
Laboratory, with original distribution at:

    https://map.nrl.navy.mil/map/pub/nrl/NRLMSIS/NRLMSISE-00/

The reference publication is:

    Picone J. M., Hedin A. E., Drob D. P., Aikin A. C. (2002),
    "NRLMSISE-00 empirical model of the atmosphere: Statistical
    comparisons and scientific issues", Journal of Geophysical
    Research, Space Physics, 2002JA009430.

All listed authors are US federal employees per the journal-
supplementary readme; the work is a product of the United States
Government and is in the public domain under 17 U.S.C. § 105.

Authorship of the model and Fortran reference:
  J. M. Picone  (Naval Research Laboratory, Hulburt Center)
  A. E. Hedin   (Naval Research Laboratory)
  D. P. Drob    (Naval Research Laboratory)
  A. C. Aikin   (NASA Goddard Space Flight Center)

K26 vendors the NRL Fortran reference under the public-domain
treatment indicated by the NRL distribution.
